<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 13 at 5:20PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A HEAVY SNOW SHOWER WILL AFFECT NORTHEASTERN TAZEWELL...NORTH
CENTRAL BLAND AND SOUTHWESTERN MERCER COUNTIES...
At 518 PM EDT, a heavy snow shower was located over Pinnacle Rock
State Park, or near Bluefield, moving southeast at 30 mph.
Gusty winds and limited visibilities will accompany this snow shower.
Locations impacted include...
Bluefield...
Bastian...
Rocky Gap...
Pocahontas...
Bramwell...
Ceres...
and Clear Fork.
Visibilities could drop quickly to less than a quarter of a mile.
Slow down and allow extra time when traveling.</description>
